The paper proposes a deep learning pipeline for recognizing and linking fine-grained location mentions in tweets, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. 

The paper also involves information retrieval and recommendation systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). 

Moreover, the paper deals with real-world Twitter data, which could place it in cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
